Convicted rapist Ched Evans will not be able to resume his football career overseas, following a Ministry of Justice intervention.

Maltese Premier League club Hibernians announced yesterday they had offered the 26-year-old former Sheffield United and Wales striker a six-month deal. 

But in a statement, the Ministry of Justice said that as a convicted sex offender on licence, Evans was effectively barred from working abroad. 

