Evans had an offer to train with his former club Sheffield United but that was retracted in November after a public outcry. 

Television presenter Charlie Webster quit as a club patron, Olympian Jessica Ennis-Hill asked for her name to be removed from one of the stands at Bramall Lane and two shirt sponsors threatened to walk.

Tranmere Rovers, Oldham Athletic and Hartlepool United have all also rejected the opportunity to sign the Wales international after showing a degree of interest. 

